            <title>[SPARK-946] Reduce memory footprint of DiskBlockManager.blockToFileSegmentMap</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-946</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;blockToFileSegmentMap right now is taking up ~400 bytes per FileSegment. In large shuffles (e.g., &amp;gt;1000 mappers/executor and &amp;gt;1000 reducers), this can lead to several GB used just for this map, which is leading to OOMs.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
